{
  "texts": [
    "Notably, this matches the standard formula for FLOP calculations in transformers Kaplan et al. (2020)",
    "For training, we use the standard Adam optimizer without weight decay, use bfloat16 precision, and train with a context length of 1024 tokens.",
    "Further details on hyperparameters are in Appendix G. Diverting from standard practice for transformers, we apply exponential decay to our learning rate.",
    "We also incorporate the auxiliary loss introduced by PaLM (Chowdhery et al., 2022), supplementing the standard cross-entropy loss function.",
    "This auxiliary loss encourages the softmax normalizer to approximate zero closely."
  ]
}